@* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
@*  Workflow 1 — Solicited                                                   *@
@* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@

<h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-1">
    <span class="badge bg-primary me-2">Workflow 1</span>
    Solicited Attachment
</h2>
<p class="text-muted mb-3">Payer creates a request &rarr; provider receives a secure upload link &rarr; provider uploads the document.</p>

<div class="row g-4 mb-5">

    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="card h-100 border-success">
            <div class="card-header bg-success text-white fw-semibold d-flex justify-content-between">
                Success path
                <span class="badge bg-white text-success">Accepted</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="text-muted small mb-3">
                    Seeded pending request <strong>ATR-2025-0001</strong> asks for
                    <em>Office Visit Notes</em> for <strong>Sarah Thompson</strong>.
                </p>
                <ol class="mb-0">
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Go to <a href="/Payer/Requests">Payer &rarr; Attachment Requests</a>.
                        Find <strong>ATR-2025-0001</strong> (status: Pending).
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Click <strong>View</strong> &rarr; copy the <em>Secure Upload Link</em>.
                        Open it in a new tab (simulates the provider receiving an email).
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        <strong>Document Type:</strong> select <code>Office Visit Notes</code>
                        (matches what the payer requested).
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        <strong>Document File:</strong> upload any small file
                        (.txt, .xml, .pdf — under 10 MB).
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        <strong>Submitted By:</strong> enter any provider name.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Click <strong>Submit Document</strong>.
                        &rarr; Redirected to Attachment Detail &rarr; <span class="badge bg-success">Accepted</span>.
                        Request ATR-2025-0001 is now <span class="badge bg-success">Fulfilled</span>.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="card h-100 border-danger">
            <div class="card-header bg-danger text-white fw-semibold d-flex justify-content-between">
                Failure — document type mismatch
                <span class="badge bg-white text-danger">ValidationFailed</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="text-muted small mb-3">
                    Provider submits the wrong document type for request <strong>ATR-2025-0002</strong>
                    (<em>Lab Results</em> for <strong>David Kim</strong>).
                </p>
                <ol class="mb-0">
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Go to <a href="/Payer/Requests">Attachment Requests</a>.
                        Find <strong>ATR-2025-0002</strong> (status: Pending).
                        Open its Secure Upload Link.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        <strong>Document Type:</strong> select <code>Office Visit Notes</code>
                        — deliberately <em>wrong</em> (request asks for "Lab Results").
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">Upload any file. Enter Submitted By.</li>
                    <li>
                        Click <strong>Submit Document</strong>.
                        &rarr; <span class="badge bg-danger">ValidationFailed</span>.<br />
                        <span class="small text-muted">Error: "Document type mismatch: payer requested 'Lab Results' but received 'Office Visit Notes'."</span>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

@* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
@*  Workflow 2 — Clearinghouse                                               *@
@* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@

<h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-1">
    <span class="badge bg-primary me-2">Workflow 2</span>
    Unsolicited via Clearinghouse
</h2>
<p class="text-muted mb-3">Provider submits to the mock clearinghouse &rarr; payer pulls &rarr; pipeline processes.</p>

<div class="row g-4 mb-5">

    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="card h-100 border-success">
            <div class="card-header bg-success text-white fw-semibold d-flex justify-content-between">
                Success path
                <span class="badge bg-white text-success">Accepted</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ol class="mb-0">
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Go to <a href="/Clearinghouse/Submit">Clearinghouse &rarr; Submit Attachment</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Enter:<br />
                        <strong>NPI:</strong> <code>9876543210</code><br />
                        <strong>Document Type:</strong> <code>Operative Report</code><br />
                        <strong>Patient Name:</strong> <code>Robert Johnson</code><br />
                        <strong>Patient DOB:</strong> <code>12/01/1960</code><br />
                        <strong>Service Date:</strong> <code>09/28/2025</code>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">Upload any file. Click <strong>Submit</strong>.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Go to <a href="/Payer/Dashboard">Payer &rarr; Dashboard</a>.
                        Click <strong>Pull from Clearinghouse</strong>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Go to <a href="/Payer/Attachments">All Attachments</a> &rarr;
                        find the new record &rarr; <span class="badge bg-success">Accepted</span>
                        matched to <strong>CLM-2025-0003</strong>.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="card h-100 border-warning">
            <div class="card-header bg-warning text-dark fw-semibold d-flex justify-content-between">
                Failure — unknown patient
                <span class="badge bg-white text-warning">MatchFailed</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ol class="mb-2">
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Go to <a href="/Clearinghouse/Submit">Clearinghouse &rarr; Submit Attachment</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Enter:<br />
                        <strong>NPI:</strong> <code>1234567890</code><br />
                        <strong>Document Type:</strong> <code>Lab Results</code><br />
                        <strong>Patient Name:</strong> <code>Unknown Patient</code><br />
                        <strong>Service Date:</strong> <code>10/15/2025</code>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">Upload any file. Click <strong>Submit</strong>.</li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Payer &rarr; Dashboard &rarr; <strong>Pull from Clearinghouse</strong>.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        &rarr; <span class="badge bg-warning text-dark">MatchFailed</span>.
                        No claim found for "Unknown Patient" with NPI 1234567890.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                <hr class="my-3" />
                <p class="fw-semibold small mb-1">Alternate — bad NPI &rarr; <span class="badge bg-danger">ValidationFailed</span></p>
                <p class="small mb-0">
                    Use NPI <code>0000000000</code> (not in registry).
                    After pull: "Provider NPI 0000000000 was not found in the NPI registry."
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

@* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@
@*  Workflow 3 — Direct / EMR                                                *@
@* ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── *@

<h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-1">
    <span class="badge bg-primary me-2">Workflow 3</span>
    Unsolicited Direct / EMR Submission
</h2>
<p class="text-muted mb-3">Provider or EMR submits directly to the payer — no payer request, no clearinghouse.</p>

<div class="row g-4 mb-5">

    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="card h-100 border-success">
            <div class="card-header bg-success text-white fw-semibold d-flex justify-content-between">
                Success — seeded EMR document
                <span class="badge bg-white text-success">Accepted</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p class="text-muted small mb-3">
                    Fastest success path — selects a pre-loaded C-CDA document that already
                    matches a seeded claim.
                </p>
                <ol class="mb-0">
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Go to <a href="/Provider/DirectSubmit">Provider &rarr; Direct Submit</a>.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        Under <strong>Select from EMR</strong>, choose:<br />
                        <code>Lab Results — John Smith (10/15/2025)</code>
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        <strong>Submitted By:</strong> enter any name (e.g., <code>Metro Health Portal</code>).
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        Click <strong>Submit from EMR</strong>.
                        &rarr; <span class="badge bg-success">Accepted</span>
                        matched to <strong>CLM-2025-0001</strong>. C-CDA structure and
                        XMLDSig signature verified.
                    </li>
                </ol>
                <hr class="my-3" />
                <p class="fw-semibold small mb-1">Alternate — file upload</p>
                <ol class="small mb-0">
                    <li class="mb-1">Upload File tab.</li>
                    <li class="mb-1">NPI: <code>1234567890</code>, Doc Type: <code>Lab Results</code>, Patient: <code>John Smith</code>, DOB: <code>03/15/1975</code>, Service Date: <code>10/15/2025</code>.</li>
                    <li>Upload any .txt file &rarr; <span class="badge bg-success">Accepted</span>.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-6">
        <div class="card border-danger mb-4">
            <div class="card-header bg-danger text-white fw-semibold d-flex justify-content-between">
                Failure — patient name doesn't match any claim
                <span class="badge bg-white text-danger">MatchFailed</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ol class="mb-0">
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        <a href="/Provider/DirectSubmit">Provider &rarr; Direct Submit</a> &rarr; Upload File tab.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        NPI: <code>1234567890</code>, Doc Type: <code>Lab Results</code>,<br />
                        Patient Name: <code>Nobody Here</code> (no matching claim),<br />
                        Service Date: <code>10/15/2025</code>.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">Upload any file.</li>
                    <li>
                        &rarr; <span class="badge bg-warning text-dark">MatchFailed</span>.
                        Payer searched NPI + patient name + service date (±7 days) — no match.
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card border-danger">
            <div class="card-header bg-danger text-white fw-semibold d-flex justify-content-between">
                Failure — NPI not in registry
                <span class="badge bg-white text-danger">ValidationFailed</span>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <ol class="mb-0">
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        <a href="/Provider/DirectSubmit">Provider &rarr; Direct Submit</a> &rarr; Upload File tab.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">
                        NPI: <code>0000000000</code>, Doc Type: <code>Lab Results</code>,<br />
                        Patient Name: <code>John Smith</code>, Service Date: <code>10/15/2025</code>.
                    </li>
                    <li class="mb-2">Upload any file.</li>
                    <li>
                        &rarr; <span class="badge bg-danger">ValidationFailed</span>.<br />
                        <span class="small text-muted">Error: "Provider NPI 0000000000 was not found in the NPI registry."</span>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

